==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Rostral
<hw>Ros"tral</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>rostralis</ets>, fr. <ets>rostrum</ets> a beak; cf. F.
<ets>rostral</ets>.]</ety> <def>Of or pertaining to the beak or snout of
an animal, or the beak of a ship; resembling a rostrum, esp., the rostra
at Rome, or their decorations.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>[Monuments] adorned with <qex>rostral</qex> crowns and naval
ornaments.</q> <rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rostrated</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Rostrate</ent>⟦br⟧
